The paper deals with quantifier elimination problems in database driven systems, which is a topic that falls under the scope of logic (cs.LO) and databases (cs.DB). The use of Knuth-Bendix completions suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and automated reasoning (cs.AI). Finally, the application of the MCMT tool to data-aware process benchmarks indicates a potential relevance to software engineering (cs.SE).
